Argentino Roca Unix Utilities
=============================

ARUU is a unified fork of sbase and ubase, it is an effort trying to
complete SBASE & UBASE., new utils partially based on toybox have
been added, specifically, the utils under cmd/net are partially based
on their toybox applet equivalent.

OVERVIEW
========

aruu builds two things:

  1. individual tool binaries (default 'make all')
  2. aruu-box: a multi-call binary containing every tool ('make box')

The multi-call binary is built by scripts/mkbox. It uses objcopy to
rename each tool's 'main' symbol, generates a C dispatch table, then
links everything into a single statically-dispatched binary. Invoke
tools by symlinking aruu-box to the tool name, or by running:

    aruu-box <command> [args...]

To install symlinks into a directory:

    aruu-box -i /usr/local/bin

REQUIREMENTS
============

  cc       POSIX.1-2008-compliant C compiler (pcc, etc)
  make     POSIX make (aruu make, pdpmake, gmake, bmake)
  ar       archive tool
  ranlib   archive indexer
  objcopy  for 'make box' only

Optional:

  yacc     only needed if rebuilding bc from bc.y

BUILDING
========

Build all individual tools:

    make

Build the multi-call binary:

    make box

Both targets can be combined:

    make all box

Configuration is in config.mk. You can override compile flags via make

INSTALL
=======

    make install           installs individual tools to $(PREFIX)/bin
    aruu-box -i /usr/bin   installs symlinks for the box binary

SOURCE LAYOUT
=============

    config.mk              build configuration
    Makefile               pdpmake-compatible build rules
    scripts/
      mkbox                builds aruu-box from compiled tool objects
      getconf.sh           generates cmd/posix/getconf.h at build time
    shared/
      *.h                  project headers (util.h, arg.h, utf.h, ...)
      libutil/             utility library (eprintf, ealloc, recurse, ...)
      libutf/              UTF-8/rune library
    cmd/
      posix/               POSIX.1-2008 tools (sh, make, grep, sed, pax, ...)
      linux/               Linux-specific tools (mount, dmesg, insmod, ...)
      net/                 networking tools (wget, ping, nc, ifconfig, ...)
      pseudo/              widely-used non-POSIX tools (tar, stat, seq, ...)
      xsi/                 XSI-extension tools (mknod, su, passwd)

TOOLS
=====

posix:
	[, awk, basename, cal, cat, chgrp, chmod, chown, cksum, cmp, comm, cp,
	cut, date, dd, df, dirname, du, echo, ed, env, expand, expr, false,
	find, fold, getconf, grep, head, id, join, kill, link, ln, logger,
	logname, ls, make, mesg, mkdir, mkfifo, mv, nice, nl, nohup, od,
	paste, pathchk, pax, printf, ps, pwd, readlink, renice, rm, rmdir,
	sed, sh, sleep, sort, split, tail, tee, test, time, touch, tr, true,
	tsort, tty, uname, unexpand, uniq, unlink, uudecode, uuencode, wc,
	who, xargs

linux:
	blkdiscard, chvt, ctrlaltdel, dmesg, eject, fallocate, free,
	freeramdisk, fsfreeze, hwclock, insmod, lsmod, lsusb, mkswap, mount,
	mountpoint, pidof, pivot_root, pwdx, readahead, rmmod, swaplabel,
	swapoff, swapon, switch_root, sysctl, umount, unshare, uptime,
	vtallow

net:
	host, httpd, ifconfig, netcat, ping, sdhcp, tftp, tunctl, wget

pseudo:
	base64, chroot, clear, cols, cron, flock, getty, halt, hostname,
	install, killall5, last, lastlog, login, md5sum, mktemp, nologin,
	pagesize, printenv, respawn, rev, seq, setsid, sha1sum, sha224sum,
	sha256sum, sha384sum, sha512-224sum, sha512-256sum, sha512sum, sponge,
	stat, tar, truncate, watch, which, whoami, xinstall, yes

xsi:
	mknod, passwd, su

